name: fruit juice
references: 1 oz. fruit juice such as liliko‘i or guava

name: guajillo chile
references: 8 dried guajillo chiles (about 2 ounces), seeds removed

name: chiles de árbol
references: 2 chiles de árbol, seeds removed, or ¼ teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes

name: sherry vinegar
references: 2 tablespoons sherry vinegar or red wine vinegar

name: red wine vinegar
references: 2 tablespoons sherry vinegar or red wine vinegar

name: red onion
references: red onions 3, 1 roughly chopped, 2 finely chopped

name: garlic
references: 3 clove grated garlic or 1 tbs garlic powder

name: ginger
references: ginger 10cm chunk, peeled and roughly chopped

name: ginger beer
references: ginger beer should be drank as a step one.

name: brioche
references: 4 slices of brioche, sourdough or plain ol’ white bread (I used brioche and sourdough in this post)

name: pork
references: 500 g pork rashers, cut into 1-5 cm pieces

name: pak choy
references: 1 bunch baby pak choy, quartered lengthways

name: thyme
references: 1 1/2 tbs dried thyme or 3 fresh thyme sprigs (remove the thyme leaves from sprig)

name: white wine
references: 300-400ml light beer or white wine (depending on the size of your crock pot)

name: ginger-preserve syrup
references: 50ml ginger-preserve syrup (serve the ginger pieces on your next cheeseboard)

name: light beer
references: 300-400ml light beer or white wine (depending on the size of your crock pot)

name: dough bread
references: Sourdough bread, vintage cheddar, Dijon mustard and rocket, to serve

name: coriander
references: 1 coriander root, or use a few coriander stalks if unavailable
½ bunch coriander, sprigs picked and finely chopped

name: bell pepper
references: 1 large bell pepper, roasted (from a jar is fine)

name: lime juice
references: lime juice, to taste (you'll need plenty)

name: sesame seed
references: 20 g toasted sesame seeds, blended with 1 g salt

name: sichuan chilli paste
references: 40 g Sichuan chilli paste (roasted Sichuan chilli oil)

name: red chilliy
references: 60 g long red chilliies, finely chopped

name: chicken breast
references: 400g chicken breast fillets, cut into 1/2 cm thick slices

name: green olive
references: 12 green olives, pitted and torn into pieces

name: caper
references: 1 1/2 tablespoons baby capers, rinsed and drained

name: cinnamon
references: ½ tsp each ground cinnamon and allspice

name: allspice
references: ½ tsp each ground cinnamon and allspice
